---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Madison Mesh" description="Building a free, community-owned mesh radio network in Madison, Wisconsin.">
	<!-- Hero Banner -->
	<section class="hero-banner" aria-label="Site hero">
		<div class="hero-overlay"></div>
		<div class="hero-content">
			<h1>We're building a free mesh radio network in Madison</h1>
			<p>
				Madison Mesh is a community of radio hobbyists connecting our city through decentralized, off-grid
				communication technology &mdash; no cell towers or internet required.
			</p>
			<div class="hero-actions">
				<a href="/getting-started" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
				<a
					href="https://discord.gg/fd3JUZc2CN"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
					class="btn btn-outline"
				>
					<svg
						xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
						viewBox="0 0 127.14 96.36"
						style="height:18px;width:auto;"
						aria-hidden="true"
					>
						<path
							fill="currentColor"
							d="M107.7 8.07A105.15 105.15 0 0 0 81.47 0a72.06 72.06 0 0 0-3.36 6.83 97.68 97.68 0 0 0-29.11 0A72.37 72.37 0 0 0 45.64 0a105.89 105.89 0 0 0-26.25 8.09C2.79 32.65-1.71 56.6.54 80.21a105.73 105.73 0 0 0 32.17 16.15 77.7 77.7 0 0 0 6.89-11.11 68.42 68.42 0 0 1-10.85-5.18c.91-.66 1.8-1.34 2.66-2a75.57 75.57 0 0 0 64.32 0c.87.71 1.76 1.39 2.66 2a68.68 68.68 0 0 1-10.87 5.19 77 77 0 0 0 6.89 11.1 105.25 105.25 0 0 0 32.19-16.14c2.64-27.38-4.51-51.11-18.9-72.15ZM42.45 65.69C36.18 65.69 31 60 31 53s5-12.74 11.43-12.74S54 46 53.89 53s-5.05 12.69-11.44 12.69Zm42.24 0C78.41 65.69 73.25 60 73.25 53s5-12.74 11.44-12.74S96.23 46 96.12 53s-5.04 12.69-11.43 12.69Z"
						></path>
					</svg>
					Join our Discord
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- What is Madison Mesh -->
	<div class="container">
		<section class="section">
			<h2>What do we do?</h2>
			<p>
				Madison Mesh is a local community of hobbyists who use "mesh" radio technologies to communicate.
				Mesh radios pass messages through a network of nodes, allowing communication without relying on
				traditional infrastructure like cell towers or internet connections.
			</p>
			<p>
				We primarily use <a href="https://meshcore.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>MeshCore</a
				>
				and <a href="https://meshtastic.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Meshtastic</a> &mdash;
				open-source firmware platforms that run on affordable LoRa radio hardware you can buy for under $50.
			</p>

			<div class="card-grid">
				<div class="card">
					<span class="card-icon">📡</span>
					<h3>Off-Grid Messaging</h3>
					<p>
						Send texts, GPS positions, and short messages across the city with no phone plan or
						internet needed.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<span class="card-icon">🔓</span>
					<h3>Free &amp; Open</h3>
					<p>
						The hardware is inexpensive, the software is open-source, and there are no fees to join
						the network.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<span class="card-icon">🤝</span>
					<h3>Community Built</h3>
					<p>Every node added by a community member makes the network stronger and extends its reach.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<span class="card-icon">🔋</span>
					<h3>Resilient</h3>
					<p>
						Because there's no central infrastructure, the network keeps working even during outages
						or emergencies.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<hr class="divider" />

		<!-- How do I join? -->
		<section class="section">
			<h2>How do I join?</h2>
			<p>
				All you need to get started is a LoRa radio ($35&ndash;$50). Visit our
				<a href="/getting-started">Getting Started</a> guide for a full walkthrough from buying hardware to sending
				your first message on the mesh.
			</p>
			<p>
				Madison Mesh primarily uses <strong>MeshCore</strong> hardware, but we also have members on Meshtastic.
				Both projects support a lot of the same devices, so you don&rsquo;t need to worry about picking the &ldquo;right&rdquo;
				one upfront.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong class="text-secondary"
					>We are actively growing the network &mdash; every new node helps! Please join us.</strong
				>
			</p>
			<a href="/getting-started" class="btn btn-primary">See the Getting Started Guide &rarr;</a>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>
